### Module 7 — HR Vault + Video + Quiz + Expiry
### REST Client file (VS Code REST Client extension / IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   1. node scripts/seedModule7.js
###   2. cd vault-server && npm run dev     (port 4001)
###   3. npm run dev                        (port 3000)
###
### Seed staff IDs: seed-admin-001, seed-mgr-001, seed-mgr-002,
###                 seed-emp-001 through seed-emp-005
###
### JWT tokens below are placeholders — replace with real tokens from your
### auth system or use the vault-server's test token helper if available.

@vaultBase = http://localhost:4001
@appBase   = http://localhost:3000

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH TOKENS (replace with real JWTs from your auth system)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@adminToken   = Bearer REPLACE_WITH_ADMIN_JWT
@managerToken = Bearer REPLACE_WITH_MANAGER_JWT
@employeeToken = Bearer REPLACE_WITH_EMPLOYEE_JWT

### Use seed staff IDs directly in x-user-id header if vault-server
### reads from that header instead of JWT sub:
@adminId   = seed-admin-001
@managerId = seed-mgr-001
@empId     = seed-emp-001


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 1: DOCUMENTS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 1.1 List all documents (admin) ---
# @name listDocs
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.2 List with search ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?search=safety
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.3 Filter by category ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?category=POLICY
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.4 Filter by status=ACTIVE ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?status=ACTIVE
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.5 Filter by warningLevel=high (critical docs) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?warningLevel=high&status=ACTIVE
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.6 Filter expired docs ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?status=EXPIRED
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.7 Pagination ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?page=1&limit=5
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.8 Get document alerts (admin/manager only) ---
# @name getAlerts
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/alerts
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.9 Get alerts as employee (expect 403) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/alerts
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 1.10 Get single document ---
# Replace DOC_ID with a real ID from listDocs response
@docId = REPLACE_WITH_DOC_ID

GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{docId}}
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.11 Upload document (multipart) ---
# Use curl for binary upload:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:4001/documents \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
#   -H "x-user-id: seed-admin-001" \
#   -F "file=@/path/to/policy.pdf" \
#   -F "title=Test Policy Upload" \
#   -F "category=POLICY" \
#   -F "accessLevel=ALL" \
#   -F "requiresAck=true" \
#   -F "expiresAt=2026-04-01T00:00:00Z"

### --- 1.12 Archive a document ---
PATCH {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{docId}}
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ARCHIVED"
}

###

### --- 1.13 Delete document (soft delete) ---
DELETE {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{docId}}
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 1.14 Employee cannot upload (expect 403) ---
# (Would require multipart — just test PATCH to show RBAC)
PATCH {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{docId}}
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ARCHIVED"
}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 2: ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 2.1 Acknowledge a document ---
# Replace with a doc ID that has requiresAck=true from seed data
@ackDocId = REPLACE_WITH_REQUIRES_ACK_DOC_ID

POST {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{ackDocId}}/acknowledge
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signature": "John Employee",
  "notes": "Reviewed and understood"
}

###

### --- 2.2 Double-acknowledge (expect 409 or idempotent 200) ---
POST {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{ackDocId}}/acknowledge
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signature": "John Employee"
}

###

### --- 2.3 List acknowledgements for a document (admin) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{ackDocId}}/acknowledgements
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 2.4 Employee cannot list acks (expect 403) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{ackDocId}}/acknowledgements
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 3: VIDEOS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 3.1 List videos ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/videos
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 3.2 Filter by category ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/videos?category=SAFETY
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 3.3 Filter by status=READY ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/videos?status=READY
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 3.4 Get single video ---
@videoId = REPLACE_WITH_VIDEO_ID

GET {{vaultBase}}/videos/{{videoId}}
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 3.5 Get video progress for current user ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/videos/{{videoId}}/progress
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 3.6 Update video progress ---
POST {{vaultBase}}/videos/{{videoId}}/progress
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "watchedSeconds": 270,
  "totalSeconds": 300,
  "percentage": 90.0,
  "completed": false,
  "lastPosition": 270,
  "sessionData": {
    "device": "desktop",
    "userAgent": "Mozilla/5.0 (test)"
  }
}

###

### --- 3.7 Mark video as completed (100%) ---
POST {{vaultBase}}/videos/{{videoId}}/progress
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "watchedSeconds": 300,
  "totalSeconds": 300,
  "percentage": 100.0,
  "completed": true,
  "lastPosition": 300,
  "sessionData": {}
}

###

### --- 3.8 Employee cannot upload video (expect 403) ---
# Multipart upload — use curl:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:4001/videos \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <employee_token>" \
#   -H "x-user-id: seed-emp-001" \
#   -F "file=@/path/to/video.mp4" \
#   -F "title=Unauthorized Upload"
# Expect: 403

### --- 3.9 Manager can upload video ---
# curl -X POST http://localhost:4001/videos \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <manager_token>" \
#   -H "x-user-id: seed-mgr-001" \
#   -F "file=@/path/to/video.mp4" \
#   -F "title=Manager Upload Test" \
#   -F "category=TRAINING" \
#   -F "accessLevel=ALL"
# Expect: 201


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 4: QUIZZES (Next.js App Routes)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 4.1 Get quiz for a video ---
# Use the Fire Safety video ID from seed (it has a quiz)
@quizVideoId = REPLACE_WITH_FIRE_SAFETY_VIDEO_ID

GET {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/{{quizVideoId}}/quiz
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 4.2 Get quiz for video with no quiz (expect 404) ---
@noQuizVideoId = REPLACE_WITH_VIDEO_WITHOUT_QUIZ_ID

GET {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/{{noQuizVideoId}}/quiz
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 4.3 Submit quiz — all correct answers (expect passed: true) ---
# Replace questionId values with actual IDs from the GET quiz response
POST {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/{{quizVideoId}}/quiz/submit
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{empId}}

{
  "answers": [
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q1_ID", "selectedOption": 0 },
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q2_ID", "selectedOption": 1 },
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q3_ID", "selectedOption": 2 }
  ]
}

###

### --- 4.4 Submit quiz — all wrong answers (expect passed: false) ---
POST {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/{{quizVideoId}}/quiz/submit
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{empId}}

{
  "answers": [
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q1_ID", "selectedOption": 3 },
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q2_ID", "selectedOption": 3 },
    { "questionId": "REPLACE_Q3_ID", "selectedOption": 3 }
  ]
}

###

### --- 4.5 Submit quiz — missing answers field (expect 400) ---
POST {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/{{quizVideoId}}/quiz/submit
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{empId}}

{}

###

### --- 4.6 Submit quiz — invalid video ID (expect 404) ---
POST {{appBase}}/api/vault/videos/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/quiz/submit
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{empId}}

{
  "answers": []
}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 5: EXPIRY CRON (manual trigger via vault-server)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 5.1 Trigger expiry job manually (if debug endpoint exists) ---
# If vault-server exposes a debug route:
POST {{vaultBase}}/debug/run-expiry-job
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 5.2 Verify warning levels after cron ---
# Should show HIGH for docs expiring ≤7 days
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?warningLevel=high
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 5.3 Verify EXPIRED docs ---
# Docs past expiresAt should be status=EXPIRED
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?status=EXPIRED
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 6: ACCESS CONTROL MATRIX
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 6.1 MANAGER_ONLY doc — employee should get 403 ---
@managerOnlyDocId = REPLACE_WITH_MANAGER_ONLY_DOC_ID

GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{managerOnlyDocId}}
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}

###

### --- 6.2 MANAGER_ONLY doc — manager should get 200 ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{managerOnlyDocId}}
Authorization: {{managerToken}}
x-user-id: {{managerId}}

###

### --- 6.3 HR_ONLY doc — manager should get 403 ---
@hrOnlyDocId = REPLACE_WITH_HR_ONLY_DOC_ID

GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{hrOnlyDocId}}
Authorization: {{managerToken}}
x-user-id: {{managerId}}

###

### --- 6.4 HR_ONLY doc — admin should get 200 ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{hrOnlyDocId}}
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 6.5 CUSTOM access — allowed staff gets 200 ---
@customDocId = REPLACE_WITH_CUSTOM_ACCESS_DOC_ID
@allowedEmpId = seed-emp-001

GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{customDocId}}
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{allowedEmpId}}

###

### --- 6.6 CUSTOM access — non-allowed staff gets 403 ---
@disallowedEmpId = seed-emp-005

GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/{{customDocId}}
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{disallowedEmpId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SECTION 7: ERROR / EDGE CASES
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### --- 7.1 Non-existent document ID (expect 404) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 7.2 Invalid UUID format (expect 400) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents/not-a-uuid
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 7.3 Invalid warningLevel value (expect 400 or empty result) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?warningLevel=extreme
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###

### --- 7.4 Progress percentage > 100 (expect 400 or clamped) ---
POST {{vaultBase}}/videos/{{videoId}}/progress
Authorization: {{employeeToken}}
x-user-id: {{empId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "watchedSeconds": 999,
  "totalSeconds": 300,
  "percentage": 150,
  "completed": true,
  "lastPosition": 300
}

###

### --- 7.5 No authorization header (expect 401) ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents

###

### --- 7.6 Search with SQL injection attempt ---
GET {{vaultBase}}/documents?search=' OR '1'='1
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
x-user-id: {{adminId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### QUICK REFERENCE — SEED IDs
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### Staff IDs (from seedModule7.js):
###   seed-admin-001    — Admin User (HR_ADMIN)
###   seed-mgr-001      — Sarah Manager (MANAGER)
###   seed-mgr-002      — David Manager (MANAGER)
###   seed-emp-001      — John Employee (EMPLOYEE)
###   seed-emp-002      — Jane Employee (EMPLOYEE)
###   seed-emp-003      — Mike Employee (EMPLOYEE)
###   seed-emp-004      — Lisa Employee (EMPLOYEE)
###   seed-emp-005      — Tom Employee (EMPLOYEE)
###
### To find seeded document/video IDs run:
###   psql $DATABASE_URL -c "SELECT id, title, \"warningLevel\", status FROM \"HrDocument\" WHERE \"uploadedBy\" = 'seed-script';"
###   psql $DATABASE_URL -c "SELECT id, title, status, category FROM \"HrVideo\" WHERE \"uploadedBy\" = 'seed-script';"
###
### Or run: node scripts/seedModule7.js --verify
